Text: Excellent.
It is the last post for this project.
This time I will start from the end it means from the achievement of the goals: .
1 / code polishing - it wasn't done to the end because Koko has found another coding solution to our final screen, and we attempted to try extended its functionality.
I think that finally, it is something that we have expected.
There is still a lot to do with the other functionality of the program, like depending on the number of errors, but the base is done.
Now the ball is on the customer side.
2 / preparing the final presentation - done!!!
More exclamation marks after sending the final report: ).
Frankly speaking,it was a long way to accomplish this task.
We had a lot of versions of our final presentation or at least a few versions of some slides.
But the deadline is the deadline - we had to be ready.
3 / preparing a document for the client describing the project - still in progress.
4 / transcripts from meetings with the focus group - Kiki made this document.
5/ passing the exam.
- could be hard to accomplish.
Just because of the exam from INFO201, I was out of the project a little bit last week.
I have prepared my tasks for the project during the weekend and on Monday.
I concentrated on my preparation for the exam up till Thursday morning.
The exam was difficult for me because of the language and too many theoretical questions.
Even if I knew the answer,Â .
I don't have time to answer all of them.
"We will see.
- this is the sentence which we were repeating permanently during the last four weeks.
I much prefer tests, even test multiply choice instead of descriptive questions.
For the final score,Â I have to wait until the 26th of June.
Far, far ahead of me.
We had another meeting with Gfactor - we showed them our solution.
Rhys gave us some tips and told us what he would like to change or add like, for example, that colors vary according to the number of errors.
He is visual; that's why he needs some color changes on the screen.
We also got feedback from the focus group.
It was positive, with only some improvements to do.
I'm so exhausted after these few weeks that my mind is empty.
I have difficulties to generate some sensible sentences and thoughts.
I will probably write in my final report some more things about the project.
Right now, I have some thoughts about all the projects and groups.
One thought comes to my mind immediately - even if the group does not choose the leader, there will always be somebody who will take somehow the leader role.
It might be very informal and could be only in some scope, like a coding leader or somebody who leads the group to the right track.
Second is that:  there are many project aspects, and it is great if the team can cooperate together, and each member of the team can have his/her hand in that work.
On the other hand, it is essential to be able to accept different ideas and solutions.
It is crucial to be able to bow your head and say that my idea is not the best one.
It is learning and development of ourselves and nice to appreciate the work of the rest of the team.
I'm not fully satisfied because I know that I could do more or differently:  for example:  to read more about visualization from R and coding in JavaScript or more about CSS.
But I met many new concepts in the field of IT and new names.
I hope that I will use this knowledge more consciously in my next project.
In the meantime, I wait for the results of my exam.
I am just curious about what happens if I do not pass this exam.
Anyway,Â  I can do nothing with it right now, just wait.
It was remarkable that most people wanted to meet after Friday's meeting during lunch.
We have spent a really lovely time together.
Thank you, Teacher1 and Teacher2, for tips, some unbiased view of the matters, and deadline reminders.
Overall
